    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 ASME V&V 40 factors. Seven factors were formally assessed; six factors were not assessed or achieved levels below required levels. The CFD model demonstrates sufficient credibility for the VAD hemolysis prediction COU based on the validation results, Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification, and mesh convergence study. The bound claim (https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou2-vad-hemolysis-acceptability) is considered supported by the totality of validation evidence presented in the validation result nodes. Decision: Accepted for regulatory submission with acknowledged credibility gaps documented.",
